history.content:
The course staff hasn't yet decided if there will be a final exam for CS 162 or not. We are aware that some students are enrolled in classes with an overlapping lecture time (e.g., CS 188). If we do decide to have a final exam during our scheduled slot during finals week, we will make sure to allow students with conflicting final exams to take their exam for CS 162 at an alternate time. CS 162 lectures will also be webcast. Thus, we hope that conflicting lecture times won't be a problem.

Source: I am part of the CS 162 course staff for Fall 2019.

See also the discussion in @9772.
